ape. The book discusses the capabilities of Bard, its strengths, weaknesses, and potential applications. Finally, you will learn how to generate a variety of Python 3 code samples via Bard.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aCOMPUTERS / Intelligence (AI) & Semantics.2bisacsh  aPython, Artificial Intelligence, Google, Gemini.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI AI COLLECTIONz978311157353308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI ASEE STEM eBook-Package 2024z978311156434008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMLI and ITGP STEM IT PACKAGEz978311157407308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024z97831115024960 cEPUBz97815015197580 cprintz978150152274140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150151974140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501519741423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501519741/original  a978-3-11-150249-6  Sciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024b2024  a978-3-11-156434-0  MLI ASEE STEM eBook-Package 2024b2024  a978-3-11-157353-3  MLI AI COLLECTION  a978-3-11-157407-3  MLI and ITGP STEM IT PACKAGE  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles